<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1615" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1615">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.5048/51.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">American Consul at Iquitos</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-29">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Department acknowledges the receipt of Mr. Fuller’s dispatch No.
                                3 of May 31, 1912, and instructs him to use care to pay for
                                everything and to accept no favors should he find that he can go on
                                no launch other than the company’s.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>